The Nigeria Customs Service Federal Operations Unit (FOU) Zone ‘B’ has made siezures of various smuggled items worth N251,701, 377.33 from various locations within it’s franchise from 24th February to 23rd March 2022. Comptroller Albasir Hamisu in charge of the FOU Zone ‘B’ in an interaction with the Media in Kaduna where the smuggled items where showcased revealed that his Unit through its gallant Officers/men and credible information from patriotic members of the public were able to seize 144 smuggled items. Among items seized were 126 parcels of Cannabis sativa (Indian hemp) along with 12 sacks of same item, 3700 sachets of Tramadol, 460 sachets of D5 Tablets, 1,100 bags of 50kg foreign parboiled rice, 18 vehicles, 41 cartons of foreign spaghetti and Macaroni. Also intercepted are 65 kegs of foreign vegetable oil (25 litres), 128 bales of foreign second hand clothings, 100 pieces of textile material, , 319 of Premium Motor Spirit (PMS) 25 litres,  336 sacks of foreign snuff (tobbaco), 11 cartons of foreign expired biscuits,13 sacks of foreign new shoes,  2,348 sacks of donkey meat which has been handed over to the Kaduna State police Command alongside a suspect for further investigation. The illicit drugs intercepted where also handed over to the National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) for further investigation. The Comptroller who said, the FOU under his command will not relent in ensuring that every smuggling activities is check mated urged smugglers to desist from.auch business and engage in more profitable business. He further appreciated the media and members of the public within Zone B for cooperating with Nigeria Customs Service and called on smugglers to desist from smuggling and embrace legitimate trade for betterment and growth of the Nigerian Economy. 